FRANK McAvennie and charity founder Lisa Hague were joined by Anthony Stokes wife Debbie and Adam Matthew's girlfriend Holly Thomas to raise funds. Frank McAvennie teams up with Celtic Wags for launch of Lola Commons Big Night Out - Daily Record FRANK McAvennie teamed up with three Celtic WAGs yesterday to launch this year’s Lola Commons Big Night Out.
Last year’s inaugural charity dinner raised &pound;40,000 for a fund set up by Lisa Hague and Hoops star Kris Commons in memory of their stillborn daughter.
Ex-striker Frank and Lisa were joined by Anthony Stokes’s wife Debbie and Adam Matthews’s girlfriend Holly Thomas.
Proceeds from Sunday’s dinner at the Hilton Glasgow will go to the SiMba charity.

 